 force).
 You may be familiar with this phenomenon if you've ever tried to slide
 an oven into or out if its usual position in a kitchen.
 It's much harder to get it to start moving than it is to keep it moving
 once it budges.
 Whether the friction is static or kinetic, it always resists motion tangential
